<subSubSection pageId="92" pageNumber="93" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="92.[151,1437,152,899]" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,314,152,179]" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. A small (
<quantity box="[431,497,153,179]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="92" pageNumber="93" unit="mm" value="6.0">6 mm</quantity>
long) parallel sided species with dark brown elytra and orange to yellow pronotum having a wide median dark marking extending to both anterior and posterior margins. LO in 
<date box="[1192,1226,189,215]" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">V7</date>
entire, with posterior margin of 
<date box="[314,348,225,251]" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">V7</date>
having a short rounded MPP.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="92.[151,1437,152,899]" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,428,260,287]" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">Male redescription</emphasis>
. 
<quantity box="[446,514,261,287]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="92" pageNumber="93" unit="mm" value="6.0">6 mm</quantity>
long. Colour (
<figureCitation box="[688,974,260,288]" captionStart="FIGURES 258−269" captionStartId="91.[151,264,1894,1919]" captionTargetBox="[213,1373,166,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@91.[213,1375,166,1875]" captionTargetPageId="91" captionText="FIGURES 258−269. Luciola horni males. 258, 259, 269 type male; 260−265, 267, 268 Halupahani male (NHML); 266 India male (Prague). 258, 266, 267 habitus dorsal; 259 habitus ventral; 260, 261, 265 aedeagal sheath: 260 ventral; 261, 265 dorsal (260, 261 under transmitted light from below); 262, 263 aedeagus: 262 ventral; 263 right lateral; 268 tergites 7, 8 dorsal; 269 label. Scale lines are 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508204" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3508204/files/figure.png" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">Figs 258, 259, 266, 267</figureCitation>
): pronotum orange to yellow with wide median dark marking extending to both anterior and posterior margins; MN and MS paler yellow; elytra very dark brown; head between eyes black (antennae and mouthparts incomplete); venter of thorax brown, legs pale yellowish-brown with slightly darker brown tarsi; ventrites anterior to LO with median darker markings, extending to sides with narrow anterolateral patch pale in 
<date box="[688,725,404,431]" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">V5</date>
, with pale lateral margin (approx.1/4 ventrite width) in 
<date box="[1354,1388,405,431]" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">V4</date>
and median dark marking occupying less than 1/3 ventrite width in 
<date box="[854,892,441,467]" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">V3</date>
; terminal tergites pale. Pronotum (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 258−269" captionStartId="91.[151,264,1894,1919]" captionTargetBox="[213,1373,166,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@91.[213,1375,166,1875]" captionTargetPageId="91" captionText="FIGURES 258−269. Luciola horni males. 258, 259, 269 type male; 260−265, 267, 268 Halupahani male (NHML); 266 India male (Prague). 258, 266, 267 habitus dorsal; 259 habitus ventral; 260, 261, 265 aedeagal sheath: 260 ventral; 261, 265 dorsal (260, 261 under transmitted light from below); 262, 263 aedeagus: 262 ventral; 263 right lateral; 268 tergites 7, 8 dorsal; 269 label. Scale lines are 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508204" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3508204/files/figure.png" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">Figs 258, 266, 267</figureCitation>
): subparallel sided, width less than humeral width. Elytron: parallel sided; interstitial lines 1, 2 visible but not as well elevated as suture. Head: GHW 
<date box="[604,639,513,539]" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">6 x</date>
SIW; ASD &lt;ASW. Antennae incomplete. Legs incomplete. Abdomen (
<figureCitation box="[160,261,548,575]" captionStart="FIGURES 258−269" captionStartId="91.[151,264,1894,1919]" captionTargetBox="[213,1373,166,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@91.[213,1375,166,1875]" captionTargetPageId="91" captionText="FIGURES 258−269. Luciola horni males. 258, 259, 269 type male; 260−265, 267, 268 Halupahani male (NHML); 266 India male (Prague). 258, 266, 267 habitus dorsal; 259 habitus ventral; 260, 261, 265 aedeagal sheath: 260 ventral; 261, 265 dorsal (260, 261 under transmitted light from below); 262, 263 aedeagus: 262 ventral; 263 right lateral; 268 tergites 7, 8 dorsal; 269 label. Scale lines are 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508204" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3508204/files/figure.png" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">Fig. 259</figureCitation>
): short rounded MPP present on 
<date box="[639,680,549,575]" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">V7.</date>
T8 (
<figureCitation box="[737,838,549,576]" captionStart="FIGURES 258−269" captionStartId="91.[151,264,1894,1919]" captionTargetBox="[213,1373,166,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@91.[213,1375,166,1875]" captionTargetPageId="91" captionText="FIGURES 258−269. Luciola horni males. 258, 259, 269 type male; 260−265, 267, 268 Halupahani male (NHML); 266 India male (Prague). 258, 266, 267 habitus dorsal; 259 habitus ventral; 260, 261, 265 aedeagal sheath: 260 ventral; 261, 265 dorsal (260, 261 under transmitted light from below); 262, 263 aedeagus: 262 ventral; 263 right lateral; 268 tergites 7, 8 dorsal; 269 label. Scale lines are 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508204" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3508204/files/figure.png" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">Fig. 268</figureCitation>
): with elongate slender anterolateral arms which are longer than the posterior entire part of T8; posterior margin entire, median area rounded and produced a little beyond rounded corners.Aedeagal sheath (
<figureCitation box="[539,751,620,647]" captionStart="FIGURES 258−269" captionStartId="91.[151,264,1894,1919]" captionTargetBox="[213,1373,166,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@91.[213,1375,166,1875]" captionTargetPageId="91" captionText="FIGURES 258−269. Luciola horni males. 258, 259, 269 type male; 260−265, 267, 268 Halupahani male (NHML); 266 India male (Prague). 258, 266, 267 habitus dorsal; 259 habitus ventral; 260, 261, 265 aedeagal sheath: 260 ventral; 261, 265 dorsal (260, 261 under transmitted light from below); 262, 263 aedeagus: 262 ventral; 263 right lateral; 268 tergites 7, 8 dorsal; 269 label. Scale lines are 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508204" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3508204/files/figure.png" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">Figs 260, 261, 265</figureCitation>
): sternite terminated by elongated medially emarginated hairy lobe; median anterior margin of tergite prolonged and apically truncate. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[1113,1279,657,684]" captionStart="FIGURES 258−269" captionStartId="91.[151,264,1894,1919]" captionTargetBox="[213,1373,166,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@91.[213,1375,166,1875]" captionTargetPageId="91" captionText="FIGURES 258−269. Luciola horni males. 258, 259, 269 type male; 260−265, 267, 268 Halupahani male (NHML); 266 India male (Prague). 258, 266, 267 habitus dorsal; 259 habitus ventral; 260, 261, 265 aedeagal sheath: 260 ventral; 261, 265 dorsal (260, 261 under transmitted light from below); 262, 263 aedeagus: 262 ventral; 263 right lateral; 268 tergites 7, 8 dorsal; 269 label. Scale lines are 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3508204" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3508204/files/figure.png" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">Figs 262−264</figureCitation>
): ML wide in basal ¾, narrowing in apical ¼ where it is ¼ as wide as basal portion; apices of LL narrowed and strongly divergent; ML considerably shorter than LL.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="92" pageNumber="93" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="92.[151,1437,152,899]" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,765,791]" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">Remarks</emphasis>
. The Indian specimen is included here because of similarities in colour pattern to the 
